FBIS4-53674 "dreas099_a_94010" FBIS-EAS-94-099 Daily Report 20 May 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Tokyo To Extend Aid Worth $34,000 to Belarus Tokyo To Extend Aid Worth $34,000 to Belarus OW2005124094 Tokyo KYODO in English 1007 GMT 20 May 94 OW2005124094 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, May 20 KYODO -- Japan will hand over medical goods and equipment worth 34,000 dollars to Belarus as emergency humanitarian assistance to help the victims of the 1986 Chernobyl accident, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [20 May]. The aid consists of about 3 tons of medical goods and equipment that can meet emergency medical demands of 30,000 people over a three-month period, the ministry said. Japan's Ambassador to Russia Koji Watanabe will hand over the goods to Belarus on Monday, it said. Watanabe will visit Belarus to present his credentials to concurrently serve as ambassador to Belarus, it said.
